1
00:00:06,670 --> 00:00:09,030
[ominous classical music plays]

2
00:00:31,390 --> 00:00:33,270
[preacher] Brothers and sisters, 

3
00:00:34,150 --> 00:00:37,590
we break this bread
to share in the body of Christ.

4
00:00:39,990 --> 00:00:41,510
Though we are many, 

5
00:00:42,070 --> 00:00:43,470
we are one.

6
00:00:43,550 --> 00:00:45,790
[all] We all share in one bread.

7
00:00:45,870 --> 00:00:47,870
[music turns pleasant and light]

8
00:00:48,910 --> 00:00:51,030
[people chatter happily]

9
00:00:51,110 --> 00:00:52,510
[children laugh]

10
00:00:53,110 --> 00:00:55,630
[preacher] And as we partake
of this holy sacrament, 

11
00:00:55,710 --> 00:01:00,830
let us remember that we share
in more than just His body and His blood.

12
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:05,190
We are blessed to live our lives
within this community, 

13
00:01:05,269 --> 00:01:09,390
where love binds us
and our families flourish.

14
00:01:13,030 --> 00:01:16,110
In His name, we have created a haven

15
00:01:16,790 --> 00:01:20,710
where our women nurture
and our men provide.

16
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:27,870
A sanctuary safe
from the temptations of the world outside

17
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:31,190
and from the evil that lies within.

18
00:01:32,190 --> 00:01:35,390
And we are eternally grateful. Amen!

19
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:36,950
[all] Amen.

20
00:01:40,710 --> 00:01:43,750
[somber theme music plays]

21
00:01:49,230 --> 00:01:51,230
[fiddler plays faintly]

22
00:01:56,790 --> 00:01:59,230
My wife, multitasker. Who'd have known?

23
00:01:59,310 --> 00:02:00,350
Idle hands and all that.

24
00:02:00,430 --> 00:02:02,510
There's no chance with you.
You haven't stopped.

25
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:05,870
[woman] Anthony, don't. Ah!
Anthony, put it-- put it down!

26
00:02:05,950 --> 00:02:07,950
That's your sister's. Ant…

27
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:10,430
Shouldn't be chasing children
in your state.

28
00:02:10,509 --> 00:02:11,830
You're about to burst.

29
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:14,390
It's all right for you.
You've only got the one.

30
00:02:14,470 --> 00:02:16,550
My kids are World War III.

31
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:19,190
[uncle, joking] Hey, uh, 
has anybody seen my favorite niece?

32
00:02:19,270 --> 00:02:20,110
[niece] I'm up here!

33
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:22,750
Oh, there she is. [laughs]

34
00:02:22,830 --> 00:02:24,470
- [uncle] Hey!
- Hey!

35
00:02:24,550 --> 00:02:25,870
[grunts]

36
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:27,430
Let me have a look.

37
00:02:27,510 --> 00:02:29,430
- [hearing aid crackles digitally]
- Yeah? You okay?

38
00:02:29,510 --> 00:02:32,230
- Yeah.
- Okay. Go play with your cousins.

39
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:33,430
[audio plays normally]

40
00:02:33,510 --> 00:02:34,750
Hey! [laughs]

41
00:02:34,830 --> 00:02:36,470
How's she getting on with the hearing aid?

42
00:02:36,550 --> 00:02:37,550
Good, we think.

43
00:02:37,630 --> 00:02:39,830
Early days. Still off in her own world.

44
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:43,430
I'd better go collect the empties.

45
00:02:46,230 --> 00:02:47,710
Raise a glass to Dad?

46
00:02:47,790 --> 00:02:49,550
[uncle sighs] He would've loved this.

47
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:51,030
[man chuckles] Yeah, he would.

48
00:02:51,110 --> 00:02:52,430
[machine whirs]

49
00:02:56,150 --> 00:02:58,350
[juices sizzle]

50
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:01,590
Ah! Look.

51
00:03:02,110 --> 00:03:04,630
- Four-leaf clover.
- [chuckles] You're lucky.

52
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:07,270
- Yeah, I am.
- Here.

53
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:09,950
Thanks.

54
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:12,270
Can you smell it? In the air.

55
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:15,510
I've always loved this feeling.

56
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:17,750
Storm's coming.

57
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:22,470
[thunder rumbles distantly]

58
00:03:23,790 --> 00:03:25,790
[people chatter happily]

59
00:03:28,230 --> 00:03:30,590
It's okay. No one's looking.

60
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:32,390
[laughs]

61
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:33,670
[shushes]

62
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,750
[all laugh]

63
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:44,470
- Anybody want an ice cream?
- Come on, kids.

64
00:03:45,070 --> 00:03:47,030
- [uncle] Ice cream time!
- Yes! Ice cream.

65
00:03:47,110 --> 00:03:49,150
[uncle] Come on, form a line.
Let's go, guys!

66
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:50,790
What's going on under here?

67
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:55,190
What have you got there?

68
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:56,470
Give it to me.

69
00:03:59,630 --> 00:04:01,070
You wicked girl.

70
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:03,750
You read unclean things, 
you'll go to hell.

71
00:04:03,830 --> 00:04:05,830
[ominous ethereal music plays]

72
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:09,430
- [thunder rumbles]
- [rain pittering]

73
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:11,550
[woman] Come over here, please.

74
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:13,190
[adults chatter indistinctly]

75
00:04:13,270 --> 00:04:16,589
[older woman] It appears that somebody
from the outside has given this to her.

76
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:19,870
I don't know how.
I've never seen it before.

77
00:04:19,950 --> 00:04:23,430
- [older woman] It's come from somewhere.
- Grace wouldn't have something like that.

78
00:04:23,510 --> 00:04:25,310
[thunder rumbles]

79
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:30,110
[lightning crashes]

80
00:04:30,190 --> 00:04:34,150
Okay, everybody, please, 
inside immediately, quickly as you can.

81
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:35,590
Thank you.

82
00:04:35,670 --> 00:04:39,390
Grace! Grace! Come on! It's the Rapture.

83
00:04:39,470 --> 00:04:40,590
The end of days!

84
00:04:40,670 --> 00:04:42,630
[hearing aid crackles digitally]

85
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:45,070
- [adults chatter nervously]
- [leaves rustle]

86
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:46,830
[ominous music intensifies]

87
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:49,790
[hearing aid emits high-pitched ring]

88
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:51,270
It's okay.

89
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:53,150
Be careful!

90
00:04:57,550 --> 00:04:59,270
[low pulsing music plays]

91
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,030
Has anyone seen Grace?

92
00:05:12,110 --> 00:05:14,030
- [man] Sorry, no.
- [woman] No, I haven't.

93
00:05:16,510 --> 00:05:18,310
[somber music plays]

94
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:21,630
Mum, is Grace with you?

95
00:05:21,710 --> 00:05:23,030
Grace? No.

96
00:05:23,110 --> 00:05:25,790
Well, she'll be inside. Don't worry.

97
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:32,350
- Adam, have you seen Grace?
- Oh, no, I thought she was with you.

98
00:05:34,030 --> 00:05:36,190
[thunder rumbles]

99
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:37,670
[lightning crashes]

100
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:47,710
Grace?

101
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:51,270
Grace?

102
00:05:54,150 --> 00:05:55,510
[panting]

103
00:06:03,550 --> 00:06:04,950
I can't find her.

104
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:06,430
[woman] She's not inside.

105
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:09,310
Adam, we've looked everywhere.
We should call the police.

106
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:12,390
No, no, no. By the time they get here, 
we'll have found her.

107
00:06:12,470 --> 00:06:14,870
She can't have gone far
with those little legs.

108
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:24,910
[music turns dramatic and fast-paced]

109
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:31,470
[screams]

110
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:33,990
[screams]

111
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:37,270
[gasps]

112
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:39,310
Help!

113
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:42,750
[man] Gather round quick.
We're losing light.

114
00:06:43,350 --> 00:06:46,190
There's a little girl
and she's lost out there somewhere.

115
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:48,230
I'm gonna split you all into four groups.

116
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:50,750
Please, let me come with you.

117
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:53,310
This is men's work. You have to stay here.

118
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:58,230
[man] The second group, 
head down to the main road.

119
00:06:58,310 --> 00:06:59,870
- They will find her.
- What if they don't?

120
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:02,470
- Do as you're told, Rosie.
- Rosie, sweetheart, you'll get cold.

121
00:07:02,550 --> 00:07:03,670
Come inside.

122
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,190
Come on.

123
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:07,630
- Hey.
- [woman] Come on.

124
00:07:07,710 --> 00:07:09,710
[man continues shouting instructions]

125
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:11,790
[dramatic music swells and plays]

126
00:07:26,230 --> 00:07:27,590
[gasps]

127
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:34,510
Mummy!

128
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:37,350
Grace?

129
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:38,990
[man] Can you hear us?

130
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,950
- Grace?
- [men in distance] Grace!

131
00:07:42,350 --> 00:07:44,390
Can you hear us, sweetheart?

132
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:45,870
Grace!

133
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:47,830
Grace?

134
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:50,150
[man in distance] Grace!

135
00:07:51,670 --> 00:07:53,230
[men continue calling in distance]

136
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:57,990
Grace!

137
00:08:07,790 --> 00:08:10,150
[music turns melancholic]

138
00:08:18,030 --> 00:08:19,550
Grace! [grunts]

139
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:23,750
Grace!

140
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:27,270
Grace! Grace, I'm coming! Help!

141
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:30,910
Help!

142
00:08:32,309 --> 00:08:33,429
Grace!

143
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:37,710
[screams] Grace!

144
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:47,910
[mellow hopeful music plays]

145
00:09:01,670 --> 00:09:02,870
[gasps]

146
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:06,670
[sobs]

147
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:11,510
[grunts] She's breathing.

148
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:12,950
[gasps]

149
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:19,870
[sobs]

150
00:09:23,790 --> 00:09:24,750
It's okay.

151
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:27,550
It's all right, darling.
It's all right. It's all right.

152
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:30,630
You're okay. You're okay, you're okay.

153
00:09:30,710 --> 00:09:33,270
Thank God you were here. Thank God.

154
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:35,950
[gentle magical music plays]

155
00:09:37,990 --> 00:09:39,990
[breathing heavily]

156
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:47,750
Mummy.

157
00:09:47,830 --> 00:09:49,550
- Grace! I'm here.
- [men] Grace!

158
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:50,790
[Rosie] We're here!

159
00:09:50,870 --> 00:09:52,710
- Found her! Grace.
- [Adam] Do you have her?

160
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:53,910
[Rosie] I've got her.

161
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:57,230
- You're okay. You're okay.
- [Adam] Hey, hey, hey!

162
00:09:57,310 --> 00:09:59,310
- Can you hear me? Can you hear me?
- Is she okay?

163
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,710
Look at me, Grace.

164
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:02,550
- Hey, sweetie. Is this blood?
- [Rosie] Grace.

165
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:05,430
- Is she hurt?
- I don't know. There was a man, he…

166
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:07,270
[Grace coughs]

167
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:10,590
We need to get her in the van.
We need to go to a hospital.

168
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:13,470
- Let's turn her over.
- [Rosie] Grace.

169
00:10:13,550 --> 00:10:15,390
- [Adam] On her side. Come on.
- Grace?

170
00:10:15,470 --> 00:10:17,750
- Adam, she's getting colder.
- I know. I know.

171
00:10:17,830 --> 00:10:20,470
- Get her on her side. Help carry her.
- Adam, careful. She's cold.

172
00:10:20,550 --> 00:10:21,390
- Isaac--
- Wait.

173
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:22,630
[tense music plays]

174
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:24,310
[dialing]

175
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:27,470
- [Rosie] It's okay. It's okay.
- [line ringing]

176
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:30,470
Hi, um, yes, ambulance, please.

177
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:38,470
[siren wails]

178
00:10:39,310 --> 00:10:41,830
- [nurse] Listen, this is-- This is A&E!
- [man] Look.

179
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:44,390
- [people chatter]
- [indistinct announcement plays]

180
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:52,110
[person coughs]

181
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:54,030
[man] Six fucking hours!

182
00:10:54,110 --> 00:10:55,910
- [nurse] Please calm down.
- No, why should I?

183
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:59,750
[video game chimes]

184
00:11:01,950 --> 00:11:02,790
[Mr. Phillips] Rosie.

185
00:11:04,590 --> 00:11:06,430
[door opens]

186
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:08,470
Mum, do you want to come back in?

187
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:12,990
Oh, just you, Mum.

188
00:11:21,470 --> 00:11:24,030
- Hey.
- Mum.

189
00:11:25,830 --> 00:11:27,350
[nurse] Here's her hearing aid.

190
00:11:27,430 --> 00:11:29,190
- This is for you.
- Thank you.

191
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:33,070
There we go. Discharge notes.

192
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:36,070
So, she's warmed up nicely.
She's breathing normally.

193
00:11:36,950 --> 00:11:38,470
She's ready to go home.

194
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:41,510
Maybe a few swimming lessons, eh, Grace?

195
00:11:41,590 --> 00:11:43,430
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

196
00:11:46,990 --> 00:11:48,350
Everything's all right.

197
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:50,990
You're not in any trouble.

198
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,670
Why did you run away, Grace?

199
00:11:56,670 --> 00:11:58,710
I was scared of the Rapture.

200
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,550
[Rosie] Oh, sweetheart.

201
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:03,350
That wasn't the Rapture.
That was just a storm.

202
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:07,790
Rapture isn't today.
It might not be for years and years.

203
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:10,550
And when it comes, 
you don't need to worry, remember?

204
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:12,550
We are the chosen ones.

205
00:12:13,070 --> 00:12:14,430
[papers rustle]

206
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:16,510
[somber music plays]

207
00:12:17,550 --> 00:12:18,990
[door opens]

208
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:21,230
[door closes]

209
00:12:23,830 --> 00:12:25,110
Let's go home.

210
00:12:47,110 --> 00:12:48,950
[engine stops, parking brake cranks]

211
00:12:52,670 --> 00:12:54,990
[men praying]

212
00:12:55,790 --> 00:12:59,790
[woman] Oh, my little darling.
You gave us such a fright.

213
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:03,190
Are you okay? Let me take her.
You must be wrung out.

214
00:13:03,270 --> 00:13:06,670
Hey. You're home.

215
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:10,910
- You're safe.
- [men] Praise be.

216
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:12,870
- That's all that matters.
- [men] Amen.

217
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,910
[women chatter indistinctly]

218
00:13:16,710 --> 00:13:17,790
[all exclaim happily]

219
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:19,310
Welcome home.

220
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:23,510
- Thank you.
- It's just a stew.

221
00:13:23,590 --> 00:13:25,510
- I got the lamb out of--
- Thank you.

222
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:30,070
[women continue chattering]

223
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:33,310
[men pray in distance]

224
00:13:34,870 --> 00:13:36,430
[men] Hallelujah!

225
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:37,510
Amen.

226
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:42,990
[men, together] Let us once again
thank our heavenly Father

227
00:13:43,070 --> 00:13:47,230
for guiding Brothers Adam and Isaac
to save little Grace.

228
00:13:47,310 --> 00:13:48,310
Praise be.

229
00:13:48,910 --> 00:13:49,790
Amen.

230
00:13:50,710 --> 00:13:52,510
And let us give thanks to our Lord…

231
00:13:52,590 --> 00:13:54,710
[prayer continues indistinctly]

232
00:13:54,790 --> 00:13:55,990
Amen.

233
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:15,670
- Mummy.
- [faucet handle squeaks]

234
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,510
What's the matter?

235
00:14:18,430 --> 00:14:19,830
Nothing, darling.

236
00:14:20,590 --> 00:14:21,910
Nothing's the matter.

237
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:24,590
What about you?

238
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:26,950
Do you need a wee?

239
00:14:29,310 --> 00:14:32,750
That man in the river, 
you saw him, didn't you?

240
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:36,590
Was he Jesus?

241
00:14:55,630 --> 00:14:58,190
You're a great mum, you know that?

242
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:01,390
Grace is lucky to have you.

243
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,190
So am I.

244
00:15:15,350 --> 00:15:16,470
[inhales]

245
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:22,590
Tired?

246
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:24,630
Yeah.

247
00:15:26,390 --> 00:15:27,470
Too tired?

248
00:15:33,230 --> 00:15:35,110
Of course, we don't have to.

249
00:15:42,590 --> 00:15:45,870
We thank Jesus
for the safe return of Grace

250
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:48,350
and ask Him to bless our union.

251
00:15:49,910 --> 00:15:52,590
To make our love clean and pure.

252
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:58,110
For it to be His will
to bless us with more children.

253
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:00,190
To be His chosen instruments.

254
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,830
To spread His love.

255
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:05,550
Amen.

256
00:16:06,110 --> 00:16:07,110
Amen.

257
00:16:10,070 --> 00:16:11,350
Turn around.

258
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,990
[sheets ruffle]

259
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:35,870
[Adam breathes heavily]

260
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:42,510
[sighs]

261
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:45,350
[dreamy music plays]

262
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,590
[Rosie breathes heavily]

263
00:17:20,390 --> 00:17:22,390
[intriguing music plays]

264
00:17:29,390 --> 00:17:31,390
[birds chirp]

265
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:54,510
[gentle solemn music plays]

266
00:18:39,950 --> 00:18:41,030
[exhales heavily]

267
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:45,150
Mummy.

268
00:18:46,190 --> 00:18:47,510
Mummy.

269
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:48,910
Where have you been?

270
00:18:49,950 --> 00:18:52,270
- Secret.
- [alarm clock beeps distantly]

271
00:18:53,910 --> 00:18:55,510
Go get ready for breakfast.

272
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:03,630
[clucking]

273
00:19:04,910 --> 00:19:06,630
Have you got the eggs, Grace?

274
00:19:07,390 --> 00:19:08,710
How many have you got?

275
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:12,110
One, two, three, four, five, six.

276
00:19:12,190 --> 00:19:13,230
- Six eggs.
- Yeah.

277
00:19:13,910 --> 00:19:14,790
Ah.

278
00:19:19,030 --> 00:19:21,030
[tense music plays]

279
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:22,790
Come on, then.

280
00:19:39,910 --> 00:19:41,750
- [man] Joseph!
- [parking brake cranks]

281
00:19:42,710 --> 00:19:44,630
[men chat indistinctly]

282
00:19:49,870 --> 00:19:54,630
Adam, before you say anything…
I just want you to know it's over, okay?

283
00:19:54,710 --> 00:19:58,270
- That's what you said last time.
- I know, but this time I mean it.

284
00:19:58,350 --> 00:20:00,790
Look, I don't want you
to worry about anything.

285
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:03,310
- But you know Rosie, she--
- She saw your phone.

286
00:20:04,390 --> 00:20:06,430
I know, and that could have been anyone.

287
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:09,110
What if it was Mr. Phillips?

288
00:20:10,190 --> 00:20:12,510
I don't want to lose you, brother.

289
00:20:15,830 --> 00:20:17,030
And you won't.

290
00:20:17,950 --> 00:20:19,190
You won't lose me.

291
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:23,710
Please take it. I don't want it.

292
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:26,270
Just get rid of it, whatever you want.

293
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:28,470
You swear it's over?

294
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:30,150
I ended it.

295
00:20:39,910 --> 00:20:43,950
Do you remember what Mr. Phillips
said to you as he left to look for Grace?

296
00:20:45,470 --> 00:20:48,350
He told me to stay there, to wait.

297
00:20:48,870 --> 00:20:50,030
And did you?

298
00:20:50,710 --> 00:20:52,790
No. I'm sorry.

299
00:20:54,070 --> 00:20:57,750
You were expressly told
to stay at the meeting hall, and yet--

300
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:58,950
I know. I know I disobeyed, 

301
00:20:59,030 --> 00:21:00,950
but if I hadn't gone, 
I wouldn't have found Grace.

302
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:03,110
Your husband, his brother were there.

303
00:21:03,190 --> 00:21:05,230
Not when she was
in the water, Mrs. Phillips.

304
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:07,630
- She would have drowned.
- Oh, come now. You don't know that.

305
00:21:07,710 --> 00:21:10,350
I do.
I was the only one there, except for…

306
00:21:14,070 --> 00:21:15,110
I'm sorry.

307
00:21:15,830 --> 00:21:19,790
I know this isn't what you want to hear, 
but it's the truth.

308
00:21:21,190 --> 00:21:23,070
It wasn't Adam or Isaac.

309
00:21:23,630 --> 00:21:26,310
There was a man in the woods, 
and he saved her.

310
00:21:31,190 --> 00:21:34,510
You should be thanking God, 
not some unchosen.

311
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:41,590
Evil exists, Rosie.
The world's lying in wickedness.

312
00:21:41,670 --> 00:21:44,350
Separation is our sole principle.

313
00:21:44,430 --> 00:21:45,950
We must live our beliefs.

314
00:21:54,790 --> 00:21:58,510
I'm sure you'll find a way
to demonstrate your repentance.

315
00:22:03,430 --> 00:22:05,910
So glad we had this little talk.

316
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:13,510
Your mummy was out early this morning, 
wasn't she?

317
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:16,350
[ominous music plays]

318
00:22:17,870 --> 00:22:19,310
Don't go to the woods again.

319
00:22:28,030 --> 00:22:30,510
[door opens and closes]

320
00:22:34,070 --> 00:22:37,270
[congregation] ♪ …and thou alone ♪

321
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:41,230
♪ Nothing in my hand I bring ♪

322
00:22:41,310 --> 00:22:45,630
♪ Simply to the cross I cling ♪

323
00:22:45,710 --> 00:22:49,950
♪ Naked, come to Thee for dress ♪

324
00:22:50,030 --> 00:22:54,350
♪ Helpless, look to Thee for grace ♪

325
00:22:54,430 --> 00:22:58,110
♪ Foul, I to the fountain fly ♪

326
00:22:58,190 --> 00:23:03,070
♪ Wash me, Savior, or I die ♪

327
00:23:08,990 --> 00:23:13,150
And now let us give thanks to God
for the rescue of young Grace

328
00:23:13,230 --> 00:23:16,390
and the bravery
of our brothers Adam and Isaac.

329
00:23:16,470 --> 00:23:19,630
Through their courage, 
He has revealed Himself to us, 

330
00:23:19,710 --> 00:23:21,510
and we are eternally grateful.

331
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:23,710
- Amen!
- [all] Amen!

332
00:23:25,470 --> 00:23:26,510
Brother Adam.

333
00:23:29,950 --> 00:23:31,470
My brother is a sinner.

334
00:23:33,270 --> 00:23:35,230
[scattered gasps]

335
00:23:37,710 --> 00:23:39,750
And the devil has a hold of his heart.

336
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:50,310
Well, stand up, Isaac.

337
00:24:04,270 --> 00:24:05,350
Is this yours?

338
00:24:10,670 --> 00:24:11,670
[sighs]

339
00:24:15,430 --> 00:24:17,710
This is not just a mobile phone.

340
00:24:19,910 --> 00:24:21,950
This is an instrument of the devil

341
00:24:23,390 --> 00:24:26,470
that opens up a pipeline of pornography

342
00:24:26,550 --> 00:24:29,950
and-- and-- and sewage to our souls.

343
00:24:30,710 --> 00:24:31,990
[tense music plays]

344
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:33,990
Mr. Crane.

345
00:24:35,910 --> 00:24:36,830
Adam.

346
00:25:03,030 --> 00:25:04,750
We must protect ourselves

347
00:25:05,270 --> 00:25:08,710
from the corrupting influence
of unclean technology.

348
00:25:08,790 --> 00:25:09,630
[breath trembles]

349
00:25:09,710 --> 00:25:13,390
[Mr. Phillips] We must ensure
we are untethered from its grasp.

350
00:25:14,030 --> 00:25:15,710
By his actions, 

351
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:20,870
Brother Isaac has endangered
our whole community.

352
00:25:21,910 --> 00:25:26,630
And… he has lost his link to his Savior.

353
00:25:33,270 --> 00:25:34,910
[music intensifies]

354
00:25:35,630 --> 00:25:37,030
[muffled sob]

355
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:39,830
All right.

356
00:25:40,590 --> 00:25:41,670
Come on.

357
00:25:44,230 --> 00:25:46,950
[Mr. Phillips] Hannah and his children
must be protected from him.

358
00:25:47,030 --> 00:25:48,510
[Hannah's breath trembles]

359
00:25:48,590 --> 00:25:50,110
He is to be silenced.

360
00:25:51,390 --> 00:25:53,230
A period of reflection…

361
00:25:55,110 --> 00:25:56,590
and repentance.

362
00:25:58,190 --> 00:26:02,470
The Lord Jesus came to seek
and save those who are lost.

363
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:09,310
May the sinner repent
and return to the fold!

364
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:12,990
[Rosie] Adam.

365
00:26:14,630 --> 00:26:16,270
How could you do that?

366
00:26:17,070 --> 00:26:18,630
How could you turn in your own brother?

367
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:20,150
How could I not?

368
00:26:20,710 --> 00:26:21,750
He had a mobile phone.

369
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:23,830
That he used to save Grace.

370
00:26:23,910 --> 00:26:25,270
This is what Isaac needs.

371
00:26:25,350 --> 00:26:26,550
What?

372
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:29,190
What about his kids?

373
00:26:29,710 --> 00:26:32,470
- Hannah, she's about to have his baby.
- I know that!

374
00:26:35,110 --> 00:26:36,750
It's complicated.

375
00:26:37,670 --> 00:26:38,990
I love my brother. You know I do.

376
00:26:39,070 --> 00:26:40,870
I know you do, 
that's why I don't understand.

377
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:42,430
[Mr. Phillips] Brother Adam.

378
00:26:42,510 --> 00:26:44,750
Adam, tell me why you've done this to him.

379
00:26:45,350 --> 00:26:47,030
I don't have to tell you anything.

380
00:26:47,710 --> 00:26:48,990
Ephesians, Chapter 5, 

381
00:26:49,070 --> 00:26:51,550
"Submit to your own husbands
as to the Lord." Maybe…

382
00:26:52,390 --> 00:26:53,590
try and remember that.

383
00:26:56,990 --> 00:26:58,990
[sweeping melancholic music plays]

384
00:27:04,070 --> 00:27:06,070
[engine starts]

385
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:07,590
[car door closes]

386
00:27:07,670 --> 00:27:09,670
[car recedes into distance]

387
00:27:33,590 --> 00:27:34,550
[keys jingle]

388
00:27:38,350 --> 00:27:39,470
[gasps]

389
00:27:39,550 --> 00:27:41,110
[man breathing heavily]

390
00:27:41,990 --> 00:27:43,830
[gentle music plays]

391
00:27:44,550 --> 00:27:45,430
I'm sorry.

392
00:27:47,030 --> 00:27:48,630
I didn't mean to scare you.

393
00:27:50,070 --> 00:27:51,990
But I need help.

394
00:27:55,990 --> 00:27:57,710
You need to go to a hospital.

395
00:27:57,790 --> 00:27:58,630
No, I can't.

396
00:28:03,230 --> 00:28:04,390
I'm in trouble.

397
00:28:13,830 --> 00:28:15,750
[man] Dettol. [chuckles]

398
00:28:16,870 --> 00:28:19,430
Oh, God, I haven't smelled that in years.

399
00:28:21,070 --> 00:28:22,950
It reminds me of me mum.

400
00:28:24,270 --> 00:28:25,310
[winces]

401
00:28:25,390 --> 00:28:26,390
Sorry.

402
00:28:28,510 --> 00:28:30,190
It needs stitches, really.

403
00:28:30,790 --> 00:28:32,230
It's a nasty wound.

404
00:28:32,310 --> 00:28:34,470
I must have caught it in the water.

405
00:28:36,310 --> 00:28:38,670
The river nearly did for both of us, eh?

406
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:42,310
She needs to be able to see your mouth.

407
00:28:42,390 --> 00:28:43,950
Grace is hard of hearing.

408
00:28:48,310 --> 00:28:49,550
Hi, Grace.

409
00:28:49,630 --> 00:28:51,150
[marker clatters softly in cup]

410
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:52,550
I'm Sam.

411
00:28:53,670 --> 00:28:55,510
I'm really glad I could help you.

412
00:28:59,950 --> 00:29:01,710
It got wet in the river.

413
00:29:01,790 --> 00:29:03,670
Now it's better.

414
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:04,630
Yeah.

415
00:29:05,870 --> 00:29:07,590
Yeah, we all feel better now.

416
00:29:12,470 --> 00:29:15,550
I'll give you some food to take with you.
Then you have to go.

417
00:29:25,470 --> 00:29:26,670
Thanks for these.

418
00:29:26,750 --> 00:29:28,510
- [Grace] Mummy!
- I'm coming!

419
00:29:31,750 --> 00:29:33,070
I'm sorry.

420
00:29:39,590 --> 00:29:41,590
[suspenseful music plays]

421
00:30:14,310 --> 00:30:15,710
Wallet, van keys.

422
00:30:18,470 --> 00:30:19,670
Isaac.

423
00:30:25,950 --> 00:30:29,990
It's okay. Come here.
Come here. [sniffles]

424
00:30:30,070 --> 00:30:31,790
[all sob gently]

425
00:30:41,590 --> 00:30:43,390
I told you it was over.

426
00:30:44,470 --> 00:30:46,190
I know you think that, brother.

427
00:30:46,270 --> 00:30:47,710
- But I--
- You betrayed me, Adam.

428
00:30:47,790 --> 00:30:48,990
I'm trying to save you.

429
00:30:49,070 --> 00:30:51,310
What? By locking me up?

430
00:30:52,110 --> 00:30:53,870
By giving you time.

431
00:30:56,750 --> 00:30:58,590
You will hear your family

432
00:30:59,110 --> 00:31:01,030
outside that door, laughing, 

433
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:02,910
crying.

434
00:31:04,150 --> 00:31:06,310
Living their lives like you don't exist.

435
00:31:08,150 --> 00:31:09,950
I want that to hurt you

436
00:31:10,630 --> 00:31:13,350
because then you will know
what you might lose.

437
00:31:13,950 --> 00:31:15,430
Do you understand?

438
00:31:17,670 --> 00:31:19,950
All of this is just for a phone.

439
00:31:21,470 --> 00:31:22,910
If they knew everything, 

440
00:31:24,230 --> 00:31:25,950
you would be disavowed.

441
00:31:26,790 --> 00:31:28,510
[tense brooding music plays]

442
00:31:28,590 --> 00:31:31,350
- You'd never see your kids again.
- [breath trembles]

443
00:31:43,990 --> 00:31:45,030
[padlock clicks]

444
00:31:49,550 --> 00:31:50,990
[sighs heavily]

445
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:55,670
[bird squawks]

446
00:31:59,510 --> 00:32:00,590
[distant scraping]

447
00:32:03,910 --> 00:32:04,910
[Rosie] Adam?

448
00:32:23,110 --> 00:32:25,270
[tense ethereal music plays]

449
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:53,070
[footsteps approaching]

450
00:33:09,270 --> 00:33:10,950
[Sam] Hi, listen, it's me.

451
00:33:13,270 --> 00:33:15,950
Look, I just need to lie
a bit low tonight, okay?

452
00:33:16,430 --> 00:33:18,870
And then I'll figure out a way
to get some wheels or something, 

453
00:33:18,950 --> 00:33:21,070
and then I'll come and find you, okay?

454
00:33:27,190 --> 00:33:29,190
[phone clatters softly on base]

455
00:33:32,470 --> 00:33:34,510
I'm sorry. I know you asked me to leave.

456
00:33:34,590 --> 00:33:37,350
My husband, he's next door.

457
00:33:38,550 --> 00:33:39,790
Please go.

458
00:33:40,950 --> 00:33:42,110
You're not allowed to be here.

459
00:33:42,190 --> 00:33:44,710
I understand, okay? I do.

460
00:33:44,790 --> 00:33:46,910
I can give you some money. Cash.

461
00:33:46,990 --> 00:33:48,790
I don't want your money.

462
00:33:52,070 --> 00:33:54,110
But I have no one.

463
00:33:56,430 --> 00:33:57,990
I've nowhere else to go.

464
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:12,710
[chickens cluck gently]

465
00:34:24,230 --> 00:34:25,670
I'm sorry it's not much.

466
00:34:27,870 --> 00:34:30,070
You have nothing to apologize for.

467
00:34:35,030 --> 00:34:37,350
I know you came back looking for me.

468
00:34:37,429 --> 00:34:39,429
[dreamy music plays]

469
00:34:41,989 --> 00:34:43,110
[chain rattles]

470
00:34:47,790 --> 00:34:50,630
And I know you feel it as well.

471
00:34:52,150 --> 00:34:53,310
I'm not like you.

472
00:34:53,389 --> 00:34:55,190
I'm not, um…

473
00:34:56,270 --> 00:34:58,350
religious or anything like that.

474
00:35:01,670 --> 00:35:04,070
I don't know why I was there
when I needed to be.

475
00:35:04,150 --> 00:35:07,630
Whether it was, uh, just luck or…

476
00:35:09,070 --> 00:35:10,190
God.

477
00:35:14,750 --> 00:35:16,110
But it meant something.

478
00:35:24,190 --> 00:35:26,750
One night. That's all.

479
00:35:28,390 --> 00:35:29,670
[clears throat softly]

480
00:35:31,710 --> 00:35:32,830
[man] Holy Spirit…

481
00:35:32,910 --> 00:35:34,470
- [men shout in distance]
- [gates clang]

482
00:35:34,550 --> 00:35:37,350
…make my heart open up to God's words.

483
00:35:38,590 --> 00:35:40,950
Make my heart open up to goodness, 

484
00:35:41,030 --> 00:35:43,550
to the beauty of God every day.

485
00:35:43,630 --> 00:35:44,470
Amen.

486
00:35:44,550 --> 00:35:46,310
[guard in distance] D-wing, all clear!

487
00:35:46,390 --> 00:35:47,790
- [gates clang]
- [guard] Lights out!

488
00:35:47,870 --> 00:35:49,710
[buzzing]

489
00:35:51,790 --> 00:35:53,150
[heavy door shuts]

490
00:35:56,630 --> 00:35:58,630
[sweeping melancholic music plays]

491
00:36:31,630 --> 00:36:32,790
[clears throat]

492
00:36:41,190 --> 00:36:43,510
We pray for Brother Isaac's soul, 

493
00:36:44,350 --> 00:36:47,390
that it will be freed
from the grasp of Satan

494
00:36:47,470 --> 00:36:51,510
and drawn back to the gentle
and ever-present light of God.

495
00:36:56,830 --> 00:37:00,190
That Isaac will see the error of his ways

496
00:37:01,990 --> 00:37:05,070
and reject the evil
that has corrupted him.

497
00:37:07,470 --> 00:37:08,510
Amen.

498
00:37:11,270 --> 00:37:12,750
[water running]

499
00:37:23,110 --> 00:37:24,190
[water stops]

500
00:37:24,990 --> 00:37:27,190
[suspenseful music plays]

501
00:37:36,630 --> 00:37:38,110
[breath trembles]

502
00:38:23,350 --> 00:38:25,350
[suspenseful music intensifies]

503
00:38:46,670 --> 00:38:48,670
[dog barks in distance]

504
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:54,270
- [people chatter]
- [announcement plays indistinctly]

505
00:38:54,870 --> 00:38:56,830
Mum, do you want to come back in?

506
00:38:58,190 --> 00:39:00,350
[reporter on TV] Police are appealing
to the public

507
00:39:00,430 --> 00:39:03,630
to help find 32-year-old Sam Devlin.

508
00:39:04,390 --> 00:39:06,310
Devlin absconded from prison

509
00:39:06,390 --> 00:39:09,910
whilst on day release
at a local fish factory.

510
00:39:09,990 --> 00:39:13,310
Anyone who sees Devlin
or knows of his whereabouts

511
00:39:13,390 --> 00:39:17,750
is asked not to approach him
and to call 999.

512
00:39:24,670 --> 00:39:25,990
[both yell and grunt]

513
00:39:28,510 --> 00:39:30,270
[groans]

514
00:39:31,510 --> 00:39:33,470
- [Sam yells]
- [groans]

515
00:39:33,550 --> 00:39:37,150
[Sam grunts]

516
00:39:38,190 --> 00:39:39,590
- [body thuds]
- [whimpers]

517
00:39:40,270 --> 00:39:42,270
[breathing heavily]

518
00:39:42,350 --> 00:39:43,510
[groans weakly]

519
00:39:45,830 --> 00:39:47,350
[groans]

520
00:39:49,790 --> 00:39:52,190
["Devil In Me" by Jamie N Commons plays]

521
00:39:52,270 --> 00:39:53,390
[groans]

522
00:40:07,030 --> 00:40:08,750
♪ I gave my life ♪

523
00:40:09,670 --> 00:40:11,190
♪ Ain't taking yours ♪

524
00:40:12,150 --> 00:40:16,150
♪ I should've let you go ♪

525
00:40:16,230 --> 00:40:17,790
[music fades]

526
00:40:21,470 --> 00:40:24,550
- [gasps]
- I cannot have a willful wife.

527
00:40:26,070 --> 00:40:27,190
[suspenseful music plays]

528
00:40:27,270 --> 00:40:29,110
[beeps]

529
00:40:29,750 --> 00:40:31,590
I need to leave. Will you help me?

530
00:40:32,670 --> 00:40:33,630
[person sighs]

531
00:40:33,710 --> 00:40:35,510
You're married, and he's an unchosen.

532
00:40:35,590 --> 00:40:37,110
[music intensifies]

533
00:40:37,190 --> 00:40:40,230
You don't want to be doing this.
